# Food Delivery App

Welcome to the **Food Delivery App**! üçîüçïüç£

This is a modern web application designed to help users easily browse restaurants, select meals, and place orders for delivery. With an intuitive user interface and seamless navigation, the app aims to provide a smooth and enjoyable food delivery experience.

## Features

- **Browse Restaurants**: Explore a wide variety of restaurants categorized by cuisine, location, and ratings.
- **Menu Options**: View detailed menus with images, prices, and descriptions of each dish.
- **Order Placement**: Easily add food items to your cart and proceed to checkout.
- **Real-time Order Tracking**: Track your delivery in real-time and receive notifications about the status of your order.
- **User Authentication**: Sign up and log in to place orders and track your past orders.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React, CSS, JavaScript, HTML
- **Backend**: (Optional: If you have a backend, e.g., Node.js or any other server)
- **Database**: (Optional: e.g., MongoDB, PostgreSQL)
- **API**: RESTful API (for fetching restaurant menus, placing orders, etc.)
- **Deployment**: GitHub Pages (for frontend), Heroku (optional for backend)

## Getting Started

To get a local copy of this project up and running on your own machine, follow these steps:

### Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following tools installed:

- **Node.js**: Make sure you have the latest LTS version of Node.js installed. You can download it from [here](https://nodejs.org/).
- **npm**: npm comes installed with Node.js, but make sure it‚Äôs up-to-date by running `npm install -g npm`.

